sentences: Judy Torres (born June 13, 1968 in The Bronx, New York City) is an American freestyle music artist and dance-pop singer.
Torres scored club hits with songs such as "Please Stay Tonight," "Come into My Arms," "Love Story," "I Love You, Will You Love Me," and her first single "No Reason to Cry."
Her debut album, Love Story, which was released in 1989 on Profile Records, is a freestyle collection, which included Ken Cedar-penned "Weakness of the Body".
Her second album, My Soul, was released in 1992 and received good reviews by critics and fans alike.
Torres previously had a regular Sunday night Freestyle show on New York's popular radio station WKTU 103.5 named "Freestyle Free for All."

In 2001, Torres scored a club hit with the sentimental love song "Back in Your Arms Again."
In 2004, she released her debut single on the label Robbins Entertainment that was titled "The Air I Breathe," which featured freestyle artist Collage.
In late 2005, Judy released the single "Faithfully."
It is a cover of a 1983 hit by the band Journey.
The single soon peaked at No. 1 as one of the requested songs on WKTU.
In August 2007, Torres returned to her Freestyle music roots with the single "I Don't."
In November 2008, Judy released "Hell, No," an anthem for abused women.
Judy Torres appears in the 2012 film Elliot Loves, in which she plays the role of Aunt Nani.
On March 18, 2018, Torres announced her one-woman off Broadway debut, No Reason To Cry, with performances scheduled for June 22 and 23 in New York City.
